        "Career": "On 12 January 2018, Ceter signed with Italian club Cagliari. He made his Serie A debut in the match against Benevento.On 28 July 2018, Ceter joined to Olbia on loan until 30 June 2019.On 8 July 2019, Ceter signed to Serie B side ChievoVerona on loan until 30 June 2020.On 8 September 2020, Ceter was loaned to Serie B side Pescara, as part of a player exchange that saw Gabriele Zappa move to Cagliari.On 26 July 2022, Ceter signed a one-year contract with Bari.On 18 October 2023, Ceter joined Virtus Verona until the end of the 2023–24 season.",
